<subSubSection pageId="178" pageNumber="457" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="178.[2062,2655,2698,3120]" lastBlockId="178.[1449,2653,3127,3475]" pageId="178" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2063,2309,2890,2923]" pageId="178" pageNumber="457">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 122 mm,tail 92 mm, ear 16 mm, hindfoot 27 mm. See general characters of the genus under the Black-and-Yellow Rice Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Goldman" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[2446,2642,3008,3041]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="178" pageNumber="457" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysomelas">M. chrysomelas</taxonomicName>
) account. The Robust Dark Rice Rat is the largest species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1902" box="[2312,2455,3087,3120]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="178" pageNumber="457" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Melanomys</taxonomicName>
, with coppery brown dorsum and a little lighter venter. Fur is close and crisp and of medium length (c.8 mm). Forefeet, hindfeet, and tail are uniformly black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
